        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-01-12T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-01-12T08:00:00-05:00" n="1147" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1147">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 EW/1–1246</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-01-12T14:00:00+01:00">January 12, 1946—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 6:23 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>191. Re Athens’ 14 to Dept, rptd Paris 1. Rueff has informed White that Greek
                    Minister here called on behalf of his Govt to inquire whether in the event
                    Greece failed to sign reparations agreement it would still be possible for Greek
                    Govt to obtain its quotas of reparations. Rueff replied “absolutely not”. The
                    Greek Minister left Rueff with the impression that he was going to recommend to
                    his Govt that agreement be signed.<note n="35" xml:id="d1147fn35">The agreement
                        was signed on behalf of the Greek Government.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Sent Dept 191; rptd Athens 3 and Berlin for Angell 17.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>[For text of the agreement on reparation from Germany, establishment of an
                        Inter-Allied Reparation Agency, and restitution of monetary gold, which
                        entered into force January 24, 1946, see Department of State, Treaties and
                        Other International Acts Series No. 1655, or 61 <pb facs="1516" n="1506" xml:id="pg_1506"/> Stat. (pt. 3) 3157. The texts of the unanimous
                        resolutions by the Conference and the Annex are printed in Department of
                        State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, January 27, 1946, pages 121–124.]</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
